ted within budget per configuration.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Provider-reported token usage for a typical document stays within the configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This depends on real AI provider execution and provider-side token accounting for the actual request. Mocked usage values would trivially pass and hide real failures in tokenization/accounting behavior. Rejected Integration: behavior text requires provider-reported live usage, not just local preflight math.","test_description":"Execute real classify() calls for representative documents and capture provider-reported usage fields. Assert reported total/request tokens are <= configured budget for each call.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When the API signals that the request rate is too high, the module waits and retries rather than returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core failure is retry-state orchestration (rate-limit signal -> backoff -> retry -> success/error mapping). A stub provider and controllable clock/backoff are sufficient; real network/OS behavior is not required. Rejected higher levels: no dependence on model output quality or multi-agentic sequencing.","test_description":"Stub provider to return rate-limit error (e.g., 429/retryable code) on first call and success on second. Verify classifier performs delayed retry and returns successful label instead of surfacing immediate error; also assert retry count/backoff contract.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
